	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Gauteng – A 24-year-old Mamelodi East man has been arrested for murder after he allegedly used a spade to hack his father to death. The man was arrested on Thursday, police spokesperson Michael Mbewe said in a statement. "It is alleged the deceased overheard the [man] and his mother arguing inside the house, when he attempted to intervene to calm the situation. "The [man] allegedly became more angered and grabbed a spade and hacked his father to death. The deceased was rushed to a local hospital." He died on arrival. The son is expected to appear in the Mamelodi Magistrate's Court soon, Mbewe said. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  